Durban - A Westville businessman became the victim of the infamous knockers gang on Tuesday. It was the second robbery on the day involving people depositing money in Durban. Captain Nqobile Gwala, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said the victim was on his way to deposit money into the bank on Buckingham Terrace when he was accosted by two robbers. She said they pointed guns at the victim and grabbed a bag containing an undisclosed amount of cash and fled the scene in their getaway vehicle. Sources told the Daily News that the businessman was held up for R42 000. A case of robbery is being investigated by Westville SAPS. The gang, so named because of their modus operandi involves targeting bank customers after they leave the premises. The gang also often follows people to the banks and rob them of their cash. Daily News